'''Henrik Sælebakke Falchener''' (born 8 May 2003) is a Norwegian footballer who plays as a [[defender (association football)|centre-back]] for [[Viking FK|Viking]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].<ref name=nff>{{NFF|3039116}}</ref><ref name=gullhelt>{{cite news|url=https://www.vg.no/sport/i/d45q1O/eliteserien-henrik-falchener-kan-bli-vikings-gullhelt-vraket-fra-guttelaget|title=Vikings «usannsynlige» gullhelt: Ble vraket fra Strømsgodsets guttelag|last=Herrebrøden|first=Øyvind|date=24 November 2025|work=VG|language=no|access-date=24 November 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
Falchener was signed by [[Viking FK|Viking]] ahead of the 2025 season, after impressing for [[Egersunds IK|Egersund]] in the 2024 [[Norwegian First Division]].<ref name=gullhelt/> After an impressive 2025 season for both Falchener and Viking, where Falchener scored six goals, most of any centre-back in the league, Viking finished top of the table for the first time in over thirty years.<ref name="NRK1">{{cite news |last1=Barka |first1=Even Hye Tytlandsvik |title=Banestorming og enorme scener da Viking vant Eliteserien |url=https://www.nrk.no/rogaland/banestorming-og-enorme-scener-da-viking-vant-eliteserien-1.17673311 |access-date=1 December 2025 |work=NRK |date=30 November 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251201151857/https://www.nrk.no/rogaland/banestorming-og-enorme-scener-da-viking-vant-eliteserien-1.17673311 |archive-date=1 December 2025 |language=nb-NO |trans-title=Pitch invasion and huge scenes as Viking win the Eliteserien}}</ref>

==International career==
On 31 March 2026, Falchener made his [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]] debut in a friendly match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rastavanger.no/viking-stopperen-fikk-sin-debut-med-haaland-og-co/s/5-165-238008|title=Viking-stopperen fikk sin debut med A-landslaget – fotballekspert spår VM-billett|work=RA Stavanger|last=Håland|first=Kirsten|language=no|date=31 March 2026|access-date=26 May 2026}}</ref> On 21 May 2026, he was named in Norway's [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/fotballvm2026/fotball-vm_-dette-er-norges-tropp-i-vm-1.17892940|title=Norges VM-tropp er klar – Dønnum og Horn Myhre vraket|work=NRK|last=Lokøy|first=Christian Dehlie|language=no|date=21 May 2026|access-date=26 May 2026}}</ref>

